result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel Michael Henderson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 2:00 PM - DA Matt Allen appears for the State of Wisconsin, Atty. Timothy Angel appears in person, Daniel Henderson appears via Zoom.  All parties can hear one another.  Def. waives right to appear in person for sentencing and wishes to proceed via Zoom. Ct. notes all parties can hear one another and proceeds via Zoom.    State recites joint recommendation:  2 days jail to be served in Clackamas County, Oregon jail to run consecutive to 15 CT 32.  Huber, electronic monitoring, if available.  Costs waived.  Defendant gives no contest plea and entered.  Defendant sworn by the Clerk.  Court accepts the joint recommendation and sentences the defendant accordingly.  Def. to report to Clackamas County, Oregon jail today by 5:00 p.m. Pacific Time.
